  "education": {
    "market_education": {
      "summary_en": "U.S. equities posted a strong risk-on session on April 24, with the NASDAQ outperforming the broader S&P 500 by nearly 2x, suggesting institutional rotation back into growth and technology. Semiconductor and AI-infrastructure names led gains as investors grew more confident in the near-term earnings outlook heading into peak reporting season. The relative strength of NASDAQ versus S&P 500 signals that risk appetite is focused specifically on high-beta tech rather than a broad market move.",
