    "daily_lesson": {
      "term": "RSI Momentum Zone",
      "explanation_en": "The Relative Strength Index (RSI) measures how fast a stock is moving up or down on a scale of 0\u2013100. An RSI between 55 and 70 is considered the 'bullish momentum zone' \u2014 strong enough to show real buying interest, but not yet overbought (above 70) where a pullback becomes more likely. Today's buys (AAOI, IREN, HIMX) all sit in this sweet spot, which is why they scored 95 while stocks with RSI above 70 scored lower despite also being technically bullish.",
